<abstract>&lt;p&gt;Part of a special issue on international perspectives on education and decolonization. The writer examines the indigenous theology practiced by the Roman Catholic church in Oaxaca, Mexico. In particular, he examines the future potential and limitations of this approach for progressive social change, especially in non-Western contexts.&lt;/p&gt;</abstract>
